  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, which typically include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal money laundering felony charges\n- Potential prison sentences (often 10-20 years)\n- Substantial financial penalties/fines\n\n2. Legal Penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Forfeiture of property gained through illegal means\n- Criminal record\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n\n3. Additional Consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n- Potential immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\nThe specific outcome depends on factors like:\n- Amount of money involved\n- Specific laundering methods\n- Prior criminal history\n- Jurisdiction of prosecution\n\nExact penalties vary by jurisdiction and specific circumstances of the case.",
